  "texts": [
    "Encoded input magic states are combined such that higher fidelity magic states are produced with some probability.",
    "For a single use of a magic-state distillation protocol, the error of an input magic state ϵ is suppressed like ϵ → ϵ d where d is a constant determined by the magic-state distillation protocol.",
    "Applying distillation recursively allows us to produce magic states with an arbitrarily high fidelity.",
    "By initializing error-suppressed magic states in the first step, where the error is suppressed as ϵ 2 we obtain a quadratic improvement in the fidelity of the output magic state.",
    "This can be performed using swap gates between adjacent qubits."
  ],
